<div id="faq" class="section">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-xs-offset-1 col-xs-10 col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-1">
				<h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-xs-offset-1 col-xs-10 col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-3">
				<h3>WRITEUPS</h3>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-xs-offset-1 col-xs-10 col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-4">	
				
				<section>
					<h4>What does CWS mean in the guidelines?</h4>
					<p><span class="bold">CWS stands for Characters with Spaces.</span> You may check the CWS of your write-up by going to Tools > Word Count if you are using Microsoft Word.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>When will the write-ups submission be?</h4>
					<p>As of the moment, the write-up submission dates are slated from <span class="bold">November 1-30.</span> Should there be any changes in the schedule, we will be announcing this through the website and/or through the Official AEGIS 2017 Facebook Page. You may also refer to the AEGIS 2017 Calendar for updates.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>Should my write-up be in first person (e.g. “I am…”) or in third person (e.g. “He is…”)?</h4>
					<p>Because this is your yearbook, we encourage all students to write using <span class="bold">any point of view they are comfortable with.</span></p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>Can I ask someone else to write my write-up for me?</h4>
					<p>Yes, you may.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>What happens if I don’t submit my write-up on time, will I still be able to submit it after the deadline?</h4>
					<p>Unfortunately, due to the tight schedule,  <span class="bold">we do not allow students to submit their write-up after the deadline</span>, unless an extension has been made. Should you fail to submit your write-up, the  <span class="bold">write-up editors will be the ones to choose what generic write-up to put on your page.</span></p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>Will we still be able to edit our write-up after we submit it?</h4>
					<p><span class="bold">We do not allow editing after the write-ups have been submitted</span>, so please make sure that the write-up you are submitting is what you want to see in your yearbook. We do, however, have an <span class="bold">online preview</span> the following semester to give students the chance to comment any <span class="bold"><span class="italic">minor</span> changes</span> they wish to make. Any <span class="italic">major </span>changes or overhauls will not be accommodated.</span></p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>What happens if I go over the CWS limit?</h4>
					<p>Should the write-up go over the CWS limit, the <span class="bold">write-up editors will be the ones to shorten it</span>, but will make sure that the essence of the write-up will be retained. If the write-up proves to be <span class="bold">too long for the write-up editor to shorten, we will be contacting you to resubmit a shorter version of your write-up.</span>However, the <span class="bold">resubmitted write-up must still be derived from the original </span>and may not be completely different write-up.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>What are examples of generic write-ups?</h4>
					<p><ul><li>“In the end, it is not the years in your life that count. It’s the life in your years.” (Lincoln, Abraham)</li><li>“That which does not kill us, makes us stronger.” (Nietzsche, Friedrich)</li><li>“It is not in the stars to hold our destiny, but in ourselves.” (Shakespeare, William)</li></ul></p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>What if I don't want my own write-up?</h4>
					<p>Even if you are not submitting your own write-up, you must still log on the website during the write-up submission period and <span class="bold">specify whether you want a generic write-up or no write-up at all</span>. Should you select the latter, the space in your yearbook page allotted for the write-up will simply be left blank.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>If I am a senior but not graduating this year, am I still required to submit a write-up?</h4>
					<p>Non-graduating students are <span class="bold">not required to submit a write-up as they will not have a write-up on the yearbook.</span> Only students who are graduating, should submit one. </p>
				</section>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-xs-offset-1 col-xs-10 col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-3">
				<h3>PHOTOSHOOT</h3>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-xs-offset-1 col-xs-10 col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-4">	
				
				<section>
					<h4>Is my photoshoot already included in the tuition payment?</h4>
					<p><span class="bold">No. </span>The cost of your photoshoot will <span class="bold">depend on the package you will select</span>. Photo packages will be released on the same day as the guidelines, which is on <span class="bold">October 1</span>. <span class="bold">Form of payment will be done on the spot</span> once you have arrived at the photoshoot venue.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>What do I do if I do not want to have my photo taken?</h4>
					<p>Graduating and non-graduating students are <span class="bold italic">not required</span> to have their photos taken. Instead, space for where their photo should be on the yearbook will be left blank.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>What are we allowed to wear/bring during the photoshoot?</h4>
					<p>Please see the guidelines to be released on or before <span class="bold">October 1</span>. This will be disseminated through the website and/or through the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/ateneoaegis2017">Official AEGIS 2017 Facebook Page</a>.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>When will photoshoot sign-ups be?</h4>
					<p>As of the moment, the photoshoot sign-up dates are slated from <span class="bold">October 3-8</span>. Further details and/or changes in the schedule, we will be announcing through the website and/or through the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/ateneoaegis2017">Official AEGIS 2017 Facebook Page</a>. You may also refer to the <a href="https://calendar.google.com/calendar/embed?src=ateneoaegis2017%40gmail.com&ctz=Asia%2FManila">AEGIS 2017 Calendar</a> for updates.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>When will the photoshoot be?</h4>
					<p>As of the moment, the photoshoot dates are slated from <span class="bold">October 17-November 18</span>. Further details and/or changes in the schedule, we will be announcing through the website and/or through the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/ateneoaegis2017">Official AEGIS 2017 Facebook Page</a>. You may also refer to the <a href="https://calendar.google.com/calendar/embed?src=ateneoaegis2017%40gmail.com&ctz=Asia%2FManila">AEGIS 2017 Calendar</a> for updates.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>Where will the photoshoot take place?</h4>
					<p>Currently, we have not yet finalized the venue for the photoshoot. <span class="bold">Details on the venue will announced on or before October 1</span> along with the guidelines.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>What time should I arrive at the venue?</h4>
					<p>For <span class="bold">individual shoots</span>, we recommend that you arrive <span class="bold">15 minutes before your time slot</span>. Should you<span class="bold"> avail of the hair and makeup</span> provided at the venue, we recommend that you <span class="bold">arrive 30 minutes before your time slot</span>. As for <span class="bold"> group shoots</span>, we recommend that your group <span class="bold">arrive 30 minutes before your time slot</span>.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>What happens if I and/or my group suddenly cannot make it to my time slot?</h4>
					<p>Should you and/or your group not be available to attend during your time slot, <span class="bold">you are allowed to reschedule your shoot</span>. To reschedule, please go to the photoshoot venue during the photoshoot proper <span class="bold">(October 17-November 18)</span>, and manually enlist in a time slot which is still available. <span class="bold">A penalty of P500 will also be collected for rescheduling.</span></p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>What happens if wasn’t able to sign-up for a time slot during the photoshoot enlistment?</h4>
					<p>If you were not able to enlist for a timeslot, <span class="bold">you are still allowed to enlist</span>. To enlist, please go to the photoshoot venue during the photoshoot proper <span class="bold">(October 17-November 18)</span>, and manually enlist in a time slot which is still available. <span class="bold">A penalty of P500 will also be collected for late enlistment.</span></p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h4>If I am a senior but not graduating this year, am I still required to have my photo taken?</h4>
					<p><span class="bold">No.</span> However, non-graduating seniors will still be part of the yearbook, but <span class="bold">only casual photos will be shown</span>. Toga photos will not be taken by non-graduating seniors.</p>
				</section>
			</div>
		</div>
